xperience.</p><p style=3D"margin: 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(54, 55, 55);line-he=
ight: 26px;font-size: 16px;">I just kind of know that there&#8217;s a Unive=
rsal Consciousness, that we&#8217;re all a part of it, and that the world i=
s more magical than we&#8217;ve been led to believe.</p><p style=3D"margin:=
 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(54, 55, 55);line-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;">This=
 is not my own idea. It&#8217;s not even a new idea. It&#8217;s a very old =
one. This is what Jesus was saying, and the Buddha, and Rumi. It is the Per=
ennial Philosophy: all major religious and spiritual traditions ultimately =
point to the same universal truth or reality. I didn&#8217;t grok that at a=
ll until two weeks ago.</p><p style=3D"margin: 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(54, 55=
, 55);line-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;"><span>In 1945, Aldous Huxley (</s=
pan><em>the </em><span>Aldous Huxley), penned a book by that name, </span><=
em><a href=3D"https://substack.com/redirect/9405db7e-adbc-42b5-b9cc-4b7f3b1=
92978?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU" r=
el=3D"" style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55);text-decoration: underline;">The Pe=
rennial Philosophy: An Interpretation of the Great Mystics, East and West</=
a></em><span>, writing:</span></p><blockquote style=3D"border-left: 4px sol=
id #0c2427;margin: 20px 0;padding: 0;"><p style=3D"margin: 0 0 20px 0;color=
: rgb(54, 55, 55);margin-left: 20px;line-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;"><em=
>The Perennial Philosophy is primarily concerned with the one, divine Reali=
ty substantial to the manifold world of things and lives and minds. But the=
 nature of this one Reality is such that it cannot be directly and immediat=
ely apprehended except by those who have chosen to fulfill certain conditio=
ns, making themselves loving, pure in heart, and poor in spirit. Why should=
 this be so? We do not know. It is just one of those facts which we have to=
 accept, whether we like them or not.</em></p></blockquote><p style=3D"marg=
in: 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(54, 55, 55);line-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;"><=
span>Huxley&#8217;s anthology, which I only began reading after listening t=
o </span><em>The Telepathy Tapes</em><span>, is one of a growing library of=
 books, videos, and experiences that all point in the same direction, back =
at the </span><em>Tapes.</em></p><p style=3D"margin: 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(=
54, 55, 55);line-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;"><span>My experiences over t=
he past month, including but certainly not limited to </span><em>The Telepa=
thy Tapes,</em><span> have made me believe a few things:</span></p><ol styl=
e=3D"margin-top: 0;padding: 0;"><li style=3D"margin: 8px 0 0 32px;"><p styl=
