line-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;">The Midwit Curve usually represents a c=
omparison of different people at the same moment in time. The very low IQ p=
erson and the really high IQ person agree. The midwit &#8211; the one just =
smart enough to overthink it &#8211; overthinks it.</p><p style=3D"margin: =
0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(54, 55, 55);line-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;">The l=
eft and right are driven by intuition; the midwit is driven by thought. The=
 left and right realize they know nothing; the midwit thinks he knows every=
thing. The left and right are unattached to their ideas; the midwit is cryi=
ng trying to convince you his are right.</p><p style=3D"margin: 0 0 20px 0;=
color: rgb(54, 55, 55);line-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;">The real beauty =
of the midwit curve, though, is that while it presents as a static thing &#=
8211; some people are just low IQ and some are just high IQ &#8211; it&#821=
7;s also dynamic.</p><p style=3D"margin: 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(54, 55, 55);=
line-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;">It&#8217;s a journey each of us goes th=
rough individually, and that we go through as a society.</p><p style=3D"mar=
gin: 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(54, 55, 55);line-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;">=
We start out knowing nothing on the left, learn a lot from books and move t=
o the middle, and then learn enough from experience, if we&#8217;re lucky, =
to end up on the right.</p><p style=3D"margin: 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(54, 55=
, 55);line-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;">From intuition due to lack of alt=
ernatives, to reason, to intuition backed by knowledge.</p><p style=3D"marg=
in: 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(54, 55, 55);line-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;"><=
strong>I think that's where we are: moving past the stranglehold of the dog=
matic rational materialist paradigm &#8211; the midwit &#8211; and towards =
something both ancient and cutting-edge: a world where technology and magic=
 coexist, where consciousness is as fundamental as matter, and where direct=
 experience matters as much as double-blind studies.</strong></p><p style=
=3D"margin: 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(54, 55, 55);line-height: 26px;font-size: =
16px;">Another way to think of it is like this:</p><p style=3D"margin: 0 0 =
20px 0;color: rgb(54, 55, 55);line-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;">2024 was =
a techno-optimist&#8217;s dream.</p><p style=3D"margin: 0 0 20px 0;color: r=
gb(54, 55, 55);line-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;">SpaceX is catching skysc=
rapers with chopsticks, Google is borrowing quantum compute from parallel u=
niverses, AI keeps getting smarter, crypto has use cases, nuclear is back o=
n the table, robots are folding laundry, cancer is under attack, autonomous=
 vehicles are driving around, and even flying cars, the thing that we were =
supposed to get instead of 140 characters, are back on the menu. The 140 ch=
aracters are humming, too. We did it, y&#8217;all.</p><p style=3D"margin: 0=
 0 20px 0;color: rgb(54, 55, 55);line-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;"><stron=
g>The future we were promised is finally here.</strong></p><p style=3D"marg=
in: 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(54, 55, 55);line-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;">I=
t feels like we&#8217;re approaching technology&#8217;s end game. The Fukuy=
aman &#8220;End of Technology.&#8221;</p><p style=3D"margin: 0 0 20px 0;col=
or: rgb(54, 55, 55);line-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;"><span>Of course, we=
 still need to build the things. We need to give the </span><a href=3D"http=
s://substack.com/redirect/f51f0e16-b6b7-481e-9a42-ded45dde92e4?j=3DeyJ1Ijoi=
OXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU" rel=3D"" style=3D"c=
olor: rgb(54, 55, 55);text-decoration: underline;">curves</a><span> time to=
 play out. But there is growing consensus on what the future looks like.</s=
pan></p><p style=3D"margin: 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(54, 55, 55);line-height: =
26px;font-size: 16px;">We will use atomic and solar energy to power abundan=
ce, travel at greater speeds with greater levels of autonomy across the glo=
be, colonize the Moon, then colonize Mars. With gene and cell therapies, we=
 will first cure disease, and then expand what the human body can do. Our a=
gents will do mundane work for us, while we do art or whatever. They&#8217;=
ll help accelerate progress in science and engineering, and speed up the in=
evitable arrival of Dyson Spheres and O&#8217;Neill Cylinders and fully com=
pliant humanoid servants with whom we will communicate via our Brain Comput=
er Interfaces.</p><p style=3D"margin: 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(54, 55, 55);lin=
e-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;">This all sounds like sci-fi, and a few yea=
rs ago, people would have told you you were crazy for believing any of it, =
but now&#8230; it seems kind of inevitable, right? A matter of when, not if=
=2E</p><p style=3D"margin: 0 0 20px 0;co=
lor: rgb(54, 55, 55);line-height: 26p=
x;font-size: 16px;"><strong>The fact that it seems so obvious, though, is a=
 sign that it </strong><em><strong>won&#8217;t </strong></em><strong>play o=
ut like that.</strong></p><p style=3D"margin: 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(54, 55,=
 55);line-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;">My hunch is that studying consciou=
sness will add new and unpredictable richness to our capabilities, and set =
us down a new branch. </p><p style=3D"margin: 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(54, 55,=
 55);line-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;">To be clear: this is just my own i=
ntuition, backed by a little knowledge and a lot of clues, as someone who i=
s in the middle of my own ride down the backside of the Midwit Rollercoaste=
r.</p><p style=3D"margin: 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(54, 55, 55);line-height: 26=
px;font-size: 16px;"><span>I do not have an airtight, falsifiable argument =
to support my intuition. I have a </span><a href=3D"https://substack.com/re=
direct/97683e74-b416-4b8c-96ce-6bc5ea7159a9?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7G=
nA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU" rel=3D"" style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 5=
5);text-decoration: underline;">cumulative case</a><span>: individually imp=
erfect pieces of evidence that, taken together, suggest something real. The=
 cumulative case argument is also known as the </span><em>argument from the=
 abundance of arguments</em><span>.</span></p><p style=3D"margin: 0 0 20px =
0;color: rgb(54, 55, 55);line-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;">This piece has=
 been the hardest for me to write of the entire year. Not in some spiritual=
 or emotional way; in a literal way: there is just an abundance of individu=
ally half-baked arguments that I need to wrangle into something coherent.</=
p><p style=3D"margin: 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(54, 55, 55);line-height: 26px;f=
ont-size: 16px;">Coherence may not be possible, so I&#8217;m just going to =
give you the stream.</p><p style=3D"margin: 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(54, 55, 5=
5);line-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;">By the end of the essay, I don&#8217=
;t want to have convinced you of anything.</p><p style=3D"margin: 0 0 20px =
0;color: rgb(54, 55, 55);line-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;">I just want to=
 spark some curiosity heading into the holiday break, and share some things=
 to read, watch, and listen to during the slowness.</p><p style=3D"margin: =
0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(54, 55, 55);line-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;">Maybe=
 you&#8217;ll feel that the world is a little more magical; maybe you&#8217=
;ll think I&#8217;m crazy.</p><p style=3D"margin: 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(54,=
 55, 55);line-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;"><span>Maybe you&#8217;ve been =
feeling the magic return yourself already and </span><em>you&#8217;ll</em><=
span> feel a little less crazy.</span></p><p style=3D"margin: 0 0 20px 0;co=
lor: rgb(54, 55, 55);line-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;">Only one way to fi=
nd out.</p><p style=3D"margin: 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(54, 55, 55);line-heigh=
t: 26px;font-size: 16px;">I&#8217;m going to take you on my own personal jo=
urney to show you how I was convinced despite the absence of peer review. T=
hen we&#8217;ll talk a little bit about why now and what it might mean.</p>=
